              "notes": "FAIL. Q1 (0.2): misidentified URL-as-permission as ReBAC - actually capability-based authZ (4th model, not previously taught explicitly). Didn't know 'anti-pattern' as a term. Taught: capability = possession-is-permission, ReBAC = explicit relationship edges. Q2 (1.0): 4/4 clean classification including the tricky (b) leaked token. Q3 (0.5): 'authorizes SP permissions following authentication' - directionally right but missed the sharper framing: SCIM doesn't do authN at all, it populates the users/groups/memberships substrate that authZ decisions read from. Queue for next review: capability-based authZ as a distinct model alongside RBAC/ABAC/ReBAC, and SCIM-as-substrate framing."
