              "notes": "FAIL (borderline). Q1 (0.7): correctly identified no loops/conditionals/functions, but described HTML as 'manipulating elements within the tree' \u2014 load-bearing misconception. HTML IS the tree (declarative noun), JavaScript manipulates it (verb). Re-emphasize: HTML is data, JS is program, DOM is the live in-browser tree. Q2 (0.75): 3/4 correct (4 elements, parent=label, required=boolean) but DID NOT ANSWER (d) about which element is void \u2014 answer is <input>. Watch for incomplete answers on multi-part questions. Q3 (0.85): clean \u2014 correctly said it won't work, no variable assignment, will render literal string 'userName'. 'Kind of tool' answer was a python input() example which is wrong medium (CLI not web) but right intuition (need a real program with variables). Used as natural segue to JSX/React."
